## Migration Strategy

### Pre-fork (week -1)
1. Deploy v0.5.10 code to all nodes (but don't run migration yet)
2. Test migration script on a testnet copy
3. Announce hard fork block height / time to all node operators
4. Prepare rollback procedure (restore from backup)

### Fork execution (coordinated)
1. All nodes stop services simultaneously
2. All nodes run `scale_balances_3600x.py`
3. All nodes flush Redis cache
4. All nodes restart with v0.5.10 code
5. Verify state root matches across nodes

### Post-fork (week +1)
1. Monitor for transaction validation errors
2. Verify all new transactions use fee=36
3. Verify CLI displays balances correctly (seconds → AIT)
4. Test faucet, auto-transfer, escrow, bridge
5. Verify staking constraints work with new values

